# Security & Privacy System

Security ensures trust in LexMastery.

Privacy ensures user control.

---

# Product Vision

System must:

- protect user data
- enforce encryption standards
- isolate AI data access
- ensure consent-based tracking
- comply with privacy expectations

---

# Architecture

SecurityController

↓

PrivacyController

↓

EncryptionService

↓

AccessControl Layer

↓

Secure Storage System

---

# Data Protection Rules

- encrypt sensitive data at rest
- secure API communication (HTTPS only)
- isolate user data per account
- no cross-user data leakage

---

# AI Privacy Rules

AI must NOT:

- store sensitive raw prompts permanently
- expose memory without permission
- infer private attributes
- share data across users

---

# Consent Management

Users must control:

- analytics tracking
- AI memory usage
- data sharing permissions

---

# Secure Storage

- encrypted local storage
- secure key management
- no plaintext sensitive data

---

# Offline Security

- local data encrypted
- sync requires authentication
- no unauthenticated access

---

# API Security

- token-based authentication
- refresh token rotation
- request validation

---

# Threat Protection

- prevent injection attacks
- sanitize inputs
- validate AI outputs

---

# Logging Rules

- no sensitive data in logs
- anonymize user identifiers
- secure log storage

---

# Error Handling

- security errors must fail safely
- no system exposure on failure

---

# Performance Rules

- encryption must be lightweight
- security checks must not block UI

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Encryption logic

Access control rules

Consent handling

Integration Tests:

Secure API flow

Privacy enforcement flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating features:

- always enforce encryption rules
- always respect user consent
- always isolate user data
- never expose sensitive data in logs or UI